The Mineral Resources and Energy Minister tables his energy budget in Parliament. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. CAPE TOWN – Mineral Resources and Energy Minister Gwede Mantashe presented his department’s 2019/20 energy budget vote. On Wednesday, Mantashe tabled the department’s mineral resources budget. READ: Mkhwebane playing politics: Mantashe Mantashe said that mining production and linked manufacturing are being hard hit by high electricity prices. Nersa approved electricity hikes for the next three years and mining companies warned that 90,000 jobs are in jeopardy because of this.